- on bootup/shutdown use `systemd` services

- on user login/logout user `systemd/User` services

- on device plug in / unplug use `udev` rules

- on time events:
    - systemd/Timers
    - Cron
    - at

- on filesystem events
    - inotify
    - incron
    - fswatch
    - systemd can activate units on filesystem events using `system.path` files.

- on shell login/logout
    - command-line shell config files

- on Xorg startup
    - xinitrc if you're starting Xorg manually with xinit  
    - xprofile if you are using a display manager

- on desktop environment startup, 
    - see XDG Autostart specification (e.g. Gnome, KDE, Xfce)

- on window manager startup
   - see XDG Autostart specification 
   - see window manager Autostart section (e.g i3)
    


